org.streaminer.stream.model

Class NominalDistributionModel<T extends Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.streaminer.stream.model.NominalDistributionModel<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Distribution<T>, Model, SelectiveDescriptionModel<T,Double>

    public class NominalDistributionModel<T extends Serializable>
extends Object
implements SelectiveDescriptionModel<T,Double>, Distribution<T>

    This class implements a histogram-model observed from a data stream. The input data elements are regarded to be nominal elements, i.e. Java Strings.

    Author:
    Christian Bockermann <chris@jwall.org>
    See Also:

      • NominalDistributionModel

        public NominalDistributionModel()
        Creates a new nominal distribution model with an infinite number of objects being tracked. Infinite here depends on available memory and is initially assumed as Integer.MAX_VALUE

      • NominalDistributionModel

        public NominalDistributionModel(int maxElements)
        Creates a new nominal distribution model. The parameter specifies the maximum number of distinct elements that will be counted in this model.

      • truncate

        public void truncate(int maxElements)

        This method trancates the size of this distribution-model by removing elements until only the given maximum number of elements resides in the count-map.

        Specifying any value < 1 for maxElements will completely prune all elements.

        maxElements -
